  "response": "190 proof Everclear is made through a distillation process that creates an extremely high alcohol concentration:\n\n1. Grain alcohol (typically made from corn) is fermented\n2. The fermented mixture is heated in a distillation column\n3. The alcohol vapors are captured and condensed\n4. Multiple distillation stages increase alcohol concentration\n5. The final product is 95% pure alcohol (190 proof)\n\nThe process requires specialized industrial equipment and precise temperature control to achieve such a high alcohol percentage. Due to its extremely high alcohol content, it's regulated in many states and not meant for direct consumption.",
